# React Spectrum house conventions

When changing code under `packages/`:

- Follow the patterns already used in the same package. Do not introduce a new abstraction for a single use.
- Do not use `any`. Any change to a public type must stay backwards compatible.
- Every behavior change must add or update a test.
- Never mutate props, state, or shared collections. Copy before sorting or reordering (for example `[...items].sort(...)`), and return new objects rather than mutating inputs.
- Match the repository's existing import ordering and formatting; do not reformat unrelated lines.
